useums in Europe, the United States, Asia, and the Middle East, Peggy Levitt offers a fresh perspective on the role of the museum in shaping citizens. Taken together, these accounts tell the fascinating story of a sea change underway in the museum world at large.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aMuseums and community. 0aMuseumsxSocial aspects. 70(DE-601)1043721330(DE-588)4281014-0aMusealisierung2gnd 70(DE-601)1062197580(DE-588)4041300-7aNationalismus2gnd 70(DE-601)1062214850(DE-588)4040795-0aMuseum2gnd 70(DE-601)3022971110(DE-588)4557997-0aGlobalisierung2gnd 7aART / Museum Studies.2bisacsh  aanthropology.  aart criticism.  aart history.  aasia.  acosmopolitanism.  acultural history.  acultural institutions.  aculture.  adiversity.  aeurope.  aexile.  afamous paintings.  aglobalization.  ahistorical artifacts.  ahistorical memory.  ahistory.  aicons.  aimmigrants.  aimmigration.  amiddle east.  amuseology.  amuseum curator.  amuseum directors.  amuseum exhibitions.  amuseum studies.  amuseums.  anational identity.  anationalism.  anonfiction.  apaintings.  apolitics.  arefugees.  aunited states.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052028606140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096145640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520961456423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520961456/original  a978-3-11-062111-2  University of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY